  "macro_shapes_comment": "Gender/phenotype axes: whole-body shapes baked by DIFFING a second MPFB human (one macro pushed off its 0.5/equal-mix default) against the committed base. MakeHuman's macro system is an interpolation grid, not single targets, so the diff uses MPFB's own macro math and stays exact. Height/proportions are deliberately absent (frame is bone-scale territory, PR #23 laws); age only goes UP from the adult base.",
  "macro_shapes": [
    { "name": "body_female", "macro": { "gender": 1.0 } },
    { "name": "body_male", "macro": { "gender": 0.0 } },
    { "name": "body_aged", "macro": { "age": 0.9 } },
    { "name": "body_heavy", "macro": { "weight": 1.0 } },
    { "name": "body_slim", "macro": { "weight": 0.0 } },
    {
      "name": "phenotype_african",
      "macro": { "race": { "african": 1.0, "asian": 0.0, "caucasian": 0.0 } }
    },
    {
      "name": "phenotype_asian",
      "macro": { "race": { "asian": 1.0, "caucasian": 0.0, "african": 0.0 } }
    },
    {
      "name": "phenotype_caucasian",
      "macro": { "race": { "caucasian": 1.0, "asian": 0.0, "african": 0.0 } }
    }
  ],
  "skins_comment": "Skins are diffuse textures from the official CC0 skins packs (release 2023-05-20: 'New CC0 skins packs'), painted on the shared MakeHuman body UV. The bake downscales each to skin_texture_size and commits it with a registry; the runtime assigns it per recipe. Names cover gender x tone x age; 'with genitals'/makeup/tattoo variants are deliberately excluded.",
